            "title": "What We Believe"
          }
        },
        "text": {
          "type": "text",
          "settings": {
            "enlarge_text": false,
            "text": "<p>In a market crowded with rushed finishes, sourced whiskey dressed up by clever labeling, and products engineered for broad, fast approval, we distinguish ourselves by going slower and thinking harder. We are skeptical of shortcuts: heavy filtration, aggressive proofing down, enormous homogenized batches, and rapid finishing windows designed more for turnover than for quality.</p><p>The goal is not simply to release whiskey, but to release whiskey at the point when it has actually become compelling. A WoodWork release should feel like something with an internal logic—something whose flavors belong together because they were guided there with real care.</p><p>We stand for the belief that the finest bottles are not the loudest, the most manipulated, or the most widely distributed, but the ones shaped with intelligence, integrity, and a genuine devotion to the craft.</p>"
